task.summary: Default task
debugging native monte carlo tree search.
fixing multiprocessing woes (pass by value when I need pass by reference)
fixed MCTS return move bug
print visit statistics after MCTS rollouts
added logging statements
messing with policy net weighting
fixed all the bugs? balanced thread pool size, weighting, etc. removed stored uct value to save space (premature optimization)
trying hacks to get garbage collector to dealloc earlier

implemented a more traditional MCTS that user the policy net when expanding nodes. sacrifices batch inference, but prevents us from expanding entire tree, and we can search to some arbitrary depth depending on best moves.
added tree height statistic
fixed win/loss bug.
fixed expanding game over node bug
no, this time I REALLY fixed it
fixed backpropagation bug, logic to choose child from UCT (minimaxing)
fixed UCT (losses / visits to infer wins/visits for parent at that node) , added better logging stats
fixed final move choice (best instead of UCT), changed default depth to 1 for more traditional MCTS
made MCTS do 2 random moves in beginning, put methods for policy net (unused) and MCTS (used) to randomly choose from set of equally successful children (if any exist)
normalized values for child updates (divide by legal children sum)
added logging for games against policy net
adding win_status updates to help for endgame moves
refactored, made MCTS class for more abstraction and to reuse game tree, made more readable, pulled up arguments to higher level scripts, efficiency tweaks
put height variable in tree nodes as height logging got out of sync from tree reuse
a lot of functional programming to update children wrt NN + pseudo BFS search
abstracted details so Expansion MCTS = EBFS MCTS with depth_limit = 0
correction, depth_limit = 1 => regular Expansion MCTS. Made it easier to assign players, better logging, fixed outstanding bugs
fixed more bugs, added logic to stop batch expansion after height threshold, rolled up iterators into single for loop (sad)

renamed functions, made number of top_children dynamic based on parent height (earlier in game = 7, mid game = 5, mid-latter = 3; numbers based on statistics taken when training NN, will titrate based on performance)
added threading for asynchronous policy net eval and cried the whole time.
added threading for tree parallelization so MCTS is always informed by NN (best approach so far). will play with pruning of lower rank children and summing of legal children instead of top children
fixing pernicious threading bugs

moved lock to keep threads from waiting too long, cleaned code, set human v computer player to be able to switch colors and to use different MCTS variants, removed double softmax in NN building, cleaned/added comments
broke up/merged some functions. made the pruning cutoff based on the probability from the NN.
fixed bugs from refactoring
keep searching even if doomed just in case.
removed huge UCTS for win/loss nodes. reduced UCT_multiplier from NN output, playing with exact weight. filter not on top children, but strictly on over 30% or within 10% of best child probability
made best_child_val the best legal child's val (forgot the policy net is model free, so a top choice may be an illegal move)
Comments for the different MCTS variants
more comments, broke up functions, integrated MCTS async into the options and had it use existing expansion wrt NN just in case we cared to use it in the future
made the stochasticity for multithreading a stochastic function of stage in the game, so that later stages are less likely to explore
works great now. too great...
fixed human v computer move. debugging pipe to play wanderer

testing EBFS MCTS (the king is back)
porting back to windows
